{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01F4ZZ8hQ4uSfaU5KxM9nyZ1","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report of all HTTP routing code related to runs endpoints.\n\n## Summary: HTTP Routing for \"Runs\" Endpoints\n\nI've completed a thorough search of the codebase for all HTTP routing related to \"runs\" endpoints. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **Route/Handler Definitions** (Main Router Setup)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 139-158)**\n\nThe handler uses Go's `http.ServeMux` with modern Go 1.22+ path pattern syntax:\n\n```\nGET /{$}                                      → handleProjectOverview\nGET /runs                                     → handleRunsList\nGET /runs/{id}                                → handleRunDetail\nGET /projects/{name}                          → handleProjectDetail\nGET /api/projects                             → handleAPIProjects\nGET /api/runs                                 → handleAPIRuns\nGET /api/runs/{id}                            → handleAPIRunDetail\nGET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output        → handleAPIStepOutput\nDELETE /api/runs/{id}/container               → handleAPIDeleteContainer\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/trigger             → handleAPITriggerOrchestrator\nGET /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator         → handleAPIOrchestratorStatus\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start  → handleAPIOrchestratorStart\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop   → handleAPIOrchestratorStop\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency → handleAPIOrchestratorConcurrency\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info                 → handleAPIProjectInfo\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff     → handleAPIPromptDiff\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows            → handleAPIWorkflows\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content → handleAPIStepContent\nGET /api/runs/{id}/stream                     → handleAPIStream (Server-Sent Events)\nGET /static/                                  → HTTP file server (static assets)\n```\n\n### 2. **URL Construction with Query Parameters**\n\n**Pattern: `/runs?project=<dir>`**\n\nUsed in three locations to filter runs by project directory:\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` (line 27)**\n  ```html\n  <a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary\">View Runs</a>\n  ```\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` (line 8)**\n  ```html\n  <a href=\"/runs?project={{.Dir}}\" class=\"btn btn-secondary btn-sm\">View all runs</a>\n  ```\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` (line 55)**\n  ```javascript\n  window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);\n  ```\n\n**Handler Implementation: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`**\n- Line 249: `handleRunsList` reads `r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n- Line 448: `handleAPIRuns` reads `r.URL.Query().Get(\"project\")`\n\n### 3. **Handler Function Details**\n\n**Key Handlers for Runs:**\n\n- **`handleRunsList` (lines 248-294)**: HTML page listing all runs, with optional project filtering via query param\n- **`handleRunDetail` (lines 376-403)**: HTML page showing single run details with steps and container status\n- **`handleAPIRuns` (lines 447-472)**: JSON API returning run list, supports `?project=` filtering\n- **`handleAPIRunDetail` (lines 525-561)**: JSON API returning single run with step details and container state\n- **`handleAPIStepOutput` (lines 563-634)**: Returns log output for a specific step (tries multiple sources: indexed logs, file system, container logs)\n- **`handleAPIDeleteContainer` (lines 636-672)**: DELETE endpoint to remove a retained container\n- **`handleAPIStream` (lines 716-775)**: Server-Sent Events stream endpoint for live/archived log viewing\n\n### 4. **HTML Templates Linking to Runs**\n\n**Template Files:**\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html`**\n  - Run list table with links to individual runs: `/runs/{{.ID}}`\n  - Project filter dropdown: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n  - API polling endpoint: `/api/runs` with optional `?project=` param\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`**\n  - Links back to runs: `/runs`\n  - SSE stream connection: `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n  - API fetch for run details: `/api/runs/{id}`\n  - API fetch for step output: `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n  - DELETE container: `/api/runs/{id}/container`\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html`**\n  - View runs for project: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n\n- **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html`**\n  - View all project runs: `/runs?project={{.Dir}}`\n\n### 5. **Server Setup and HTTP Listener**\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` (lines 101-122)**\n\n```go\nvar httpServer *http.Server\nif httpAddr := envOrConfig(\"CLOCHE_HTTP\", globalCfg.Daemon.HTTP, \"\"); httpAddr != \"\" {\n    webOpts := []web.HandlerOption{...}\n    webHandler, err := web.NewHandler(store, store, webOpts...)\n    httpServer = &http.Server{Addr: httpAddr, Handler: webHandler}\n    // Listen and serve in background\n}\n```\n\n### 6. **Client-Side HTTP References**\n\n**File: `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (line 315)**\n\nCLI client constructs SSE URL for log following:\n```go\nsseURL := fmt.Sprintf(\"http://%s/api/runs/%s/stream\", httpAddr, runID)\n```\n\nReads from `CLOCHE_HTTP` environment variable (defaults to `localhost:8080`)\n\n### 7. **Test Coverage**\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go`**\n\nTests confirm route handling:\n- Line 92: `GET /runs` (no filter)\n- Line 130: `GET /runs/run-detail-1`\n- Line 155: `GET /api/runs`\n- Line 186: `GET /api/runs/api-detail-1`\n- Line 286: `GET /runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (with filter)\n- Line 315/325: `GET /api/runs?project=/home/user/alpha` (API with filter)\n\n**File: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`**\n\nTests confirm streaming:\n- Line 56: `GET /api/runs/sse-test-1/stream`\n- Line 126: HTTP client test for SSE stream\n- Line 159: 404 handling for nonexistent run stream\n\n### 8. **Related Issue**\n\n**File: `/workspace/.beads/issues.jsonl`**\n\nThere is an open issue (cloche-9lt) marked as \"in_progress\" to refactor the URL structure:\n> \"Move project runs URL to projects/<project>/runs\" (currently at `runs?project=...`)\n\n### Key Architectural Details:\n\n- **Mux Type**: `http.ServeMux` (Go 1.22+ with method prefixes)\n- **Request Patterns**: Modern Go path pattern syntax with named segments (e.g., `{id}`, `{step}`)\n- **Query Parameters**: Support for `?project=<dir>` to filter runs by project directory\n- **Content Types**: HTML for UI routes, JSON for API routes, Server-Sent Events for streaming\n- **Stream Handling**: SSE endpoint serves either archived `full.log` for completed runs or live stream for active runs\n\n**Absolute File Paths:**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` - Main route definitions and handlers\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html` - Runs list template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` - Single run detail template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/projects.html` - Projects overview template\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/project_detail.html` - Project detail template\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloched/main.go` - HTTP server setup\n- `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` - CLI client with SSE stream URL construction\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_test.go` - Route handler tests\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go` - SSE streaming tests"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aea0f76029e2e802c (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 69104\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 41194</usage>"}]}]},"parent_to