{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019cdh6X2eDmYPLNmenEbSLu","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→{{define \"content\"}}\n     2→<h1>Runs</h1>\n     3→{{if .Projects}}\n     4→<div class=\"project-filter\">\n     5→    <label for=\"project-select\">Project:</label>\n     6→    <select id=\"project-select\" onchange=\"filterByProject(this.value)\">\n     7→        <option value=\"\">All projects</option>\n     8→        {{range .Projects}}\n     9→        <option value=\"{{.Dir}}\"{{if eq .Dir $.ProjectFilter}} selected{{end}}>{{.Label}}{{if .ContainerCount}} ({{.ContainerCount}} container{{if gt .ContainerCount 1}}s{{end}}){{end}}</option>\n    10→        {{end}}\n    11→    </select>\n    12→</div>\n    13→{{end}}\n    14→<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    15→    <thead>\n    16→        <tr>\n    17→            <th>Run ID</th>\n    18→            <th>Project</th>\n    19→            <th>Workflow</th>\n    20→            <th>State</th>\n    21→            <th>Started</th>\n    22→            <th>Completed</th>\n    23→            <th>Container</th>\n    24→            <th>Error</th>\n    25→        </tr>\n    26→    </thead>\n    27→    <tbody id=\"runs-body\">\n    28→    {{if .Runs}}\n    29→        {{range .Runs}}\n    30→        <tr>\n    31→            <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n    32→            <td>{{index $.ProjectLabels .ProjectDir}}</td>\n    33→            <td>{{.WorkflowName}}</td>\n    34→            <td><span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .State}}\">{{.State}}</span></td>\n    35→            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n    36→            <td>{{formatTime .CompletedAt}}</td>\n    37→            <td class=\"mono\">{{shortContainerID .ContainerID}}</td>\n    38→            <td class=\"error-cell\">{{truncate .ErrorMessage 80}}</td>\n    39→        </tr>\n    40→        {{end}}\n    41→    {{else}}\n    42→        <tr><td colspan=\"8\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>\n    43→    {{end}}\n    44→    </tbody>\n    45→</table>\n    46→{{end}}\n    47→\n    48→{{define \"scripts\"}}\n    49→<script>\n    50→(function() {\n    51→    var currentProject = '{{.ProjectFilter}}';\n    52→\n    53→    function filterByProject(dir) {\n    54→        if (dir) {\n    55→            window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);\n    56→        } else {\n    57→            window.location.href = '/runs';\n    58→        }\n    59→    }\n    60→    window.filterByProject = filterByProject;\n    61→\n    62→    function poll() {\n    63→        var url = '/api/runs';\n    64→        if (currentProject) {\n    65→            url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);\n    66→        }\n    67→        fetch(url)\n    68→            .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n    69→            .then(function(runs) {\n    70→                var tbody = document.getElementById('runs-body');\n    71→                if (!runs || runs.length === 0) {\n    72→                    tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"8\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>';\n    73→                    return;\n    74→                }\n    75→                var html = '';\n    76→                for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n    77→                    var r = runs[i];\n    78→                    var cid = r.container_id || '';\n    79→                    if (cid.length > 12) cid = cid.substring(0, 12);\n    80→                    var err = r.error_message || '';\n    81→                    if (err.length > 80) err = err.substring(0, 80) + '...';\n    82→                    var proj = r.project_label || '';\n    83→                    html += '<tr>' +\n    84→                        '<td><a href=\"/runs/' + r.id + '\">' + r.id + '</a></td>' +\n    85→                        '<td>' + escapeHtml(proj) + '</td>' +\n    86→                        '<td>' + r.workflow_name + '</td>' +\n    87→                        '<td><span class=\"badge badge-' + r.state + '\">' + r.state + '</span></td>' +\n    88→                        '<td>' + r.started_at + '</td>' +\n    89→                        '<td>' + r.completed_at + '</td>' +\n    90→                        '<td class=\"mono\">' + cid + '</td>' +\n    91→                        '<td class=\"error-cell\">' + escapeHtml(err) + '</td>' +\n    92→                        '</tr>';\n    93→                }\n    94→                tbody.innerHTML = html;\n    95→            })\n    96→            .catch(function() {});\n    97→    }\n    98→    function escapeHtml(s) {\n    99→        var d = document.createElement('div');\n   100→        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n   101→        return d.innerHTML;\n   102→    }\n   103→    setInterval(poll, 3000);\n   104→})();\n   105→</script>\n   106→{{end}}\n   107→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c74eec70-10cc-489a-bef5-b2195fdf4510","uuid":"574ad8cb-1a4e-46a4-85aa-c5520aa2eb16","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/runs.html","content":"{{define \"content\"}}\n<h1>Runs</h1>\n{{if .Projects}}\n<div class=\"project-filter\">\n    <label for=\"project-select\">Project:</label>\n    <select id=\"project-select\" onchange=\"filterByProject(this.value)\">\n        <option value=\"\">All projects</option>\n        {{range .Projects}}\n        <option value=\"{{.Dir}}\"{{if eq .Dir $.ProjectFilter}} selected{{end}}>{{.Label}}{{if .ContainerCount}} ({{.ContainerCount}} container{{if gt .ContainerCount 1}}s{{end}}){{end}}</option>\n        {{end}}\n    </select>\n</div>\n{{end}}\n<table class=\"runs-table\">\n    <thead>\n        <tr>\n            <th>Run ID</th>\n            <th>Project</th>\n            <th>Workflow</th>\n            <th>State</th>\n            <th>Started</th>\n            <th>Completed</th>\n            <th>Container</th>\n            <th>Error</th>\n        </tr>\n    </thead>\n    <tbody id=\"runs-body\">\n    {{if .Runs}}\n        {{range .Runs}}\n        <tr>\n            <td><a href=\"/runs/{{.ID}}\">{{.ID}}</a></td>\n            <td>{{index $.ProjectLabels .ProjectDir}}</td>\n            <td>{{.WorkflowName}}</td>\n            <td><span class=\"badge badge-{{stateColor .State}}\">{{.State}}</span></td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .StartedAt}}</td>\n            <td>{{formatTime .CompletedAt}}</td>\n            <td class=\"mono\">{{shortContainerID .ContainerID}}</td>\n            <td class=\"error-cell\">{{truncate .ErrorMessage 80}}</td>\n        </tr>\n        {{end}}\n    {{else}}\n        <tr><td colspan=\"8\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>\n    {{end}}\n    </tbody>\n</table>\n{{end}}\n\n{{define \"scripts\"}}\n<script>\n(function() {\n    var currentProject = '{{.ProjectFilter}}';\n\n    function filterByProject(dir) {\n        if (dir) {\n            window.location.href = '/runs?project=' + encodeURIComponent(dir);\n        } else {\n            window.location.href = '/runs';\n        }\n    }\n    window.filterByProject = filterByProject;\n\n    function poll() {\n        var url = '/api/runs';\n        if (currentProject) {\n            url += '?project=' + encodeURIComponent(currentProject);\n        }\n        fetch(url)\n            .then(function(r) { return r.json(); })\n            .then(function(runs) {\n                var tbody = document.getElementById('runs-body');\n                if (!runs || runs.length === 0) {\n                    tbody.innerHTML = '<tr><td colspan=\"8\" class=\"empty\">No runs yet.</td></tr>';\n                    return;\n                }\n                var html = '';\n                for (var i = 0; i < runs.length; i++) {\n                    var r = runs[i];\n                    var cid = r.container_id || '';\n                    if (cid.length > 12) cid = cid.substring(0, 12);\n                    var err = r.error_message || '';\n                    if (err.length > 80) err = err.substring(0, 80) + '...';\n                    var proj = r.project_label || '';\n                    html += '<tr>' +\n                        '<td><a href=\"/runs/' + r.id + '\">' + r.id + '</a></td>' +\n                        '<td>' + escapeHtml(proj) + '</td>' +\n                        '<td>' + r.workflow_name + '</td>' +\n                        '<td><span class=\"badge badge-' + r.state + '\">' + r.state + '</span></td>' +\n                        '<td>' + r.started_at + '</td>' +\n                        '<td>' + r.completed_at + '</td>' +\n                        '<td class=\"mono\">' + cid + '</td>' +\n                        '<td class=\"error-cell\">' + escapeHtml(err) + '</td>' +\n                        '</tr>';\n                }\n                tbody.innerHTML = html;\n            })\n            .catch(function() {});\n    }\n    function escapeHtml(s) {\n        var d = document.createElement('div');\n        d.appendChild(document.createTextNode(s));\n        return d.innerHTML;\n    }\n    setInterval(poll, 3000);\n})();\n</script>\n{{end}}\n","numLines":107,"startLine":1,"totalLines":107}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_012sCQjgiBVuAcEP74EwW19M","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture. I need to:\n\n1. Add new routes: `GET /projects/{name}/runs` (HTML) and `GET /api/projects/{name}/runs` (API)\n2. Update the handlers to extract the project name from the URL path instead of query params\n3. Update templates to link to `/projects/{label}/runs` instead of `/runs?project={dir}`\n4. Update the JavaScript filter function to use the new URL\n5. Update tests\n\nThe key insight is that the current `?project=` param uses the project **directory** path, but the new URL uses the project **label** (name). So I need to modify the handler to resolve the label to a directory.\n\n\nI'm planning the handler changes: I'll add the two new routes for the project-specific runs endpoints, keep the existing `/runs` routes for unfiltered access, and split the logic so the filtered case goes through the new project-specific paths. I can reuse the existing `handleRunsList` logic by extracting the core filtering and rendering into a shared function, then have both the all-runs and project-filtered handlers call it with the appropriate project filter.\n\nThe runs template's project dropdown needs to know the current project label so it can construct the right redirect URL when a new project is selected. I should pass the current project label to the template context, and update the dropdown's redirect logic to use `/projects/{label}/runs` instead of the query parameter approach. the `?project=` filtering from it (or keep it for backward compat but update all links). The simplest approach is to add new routes with dedicated handlers while keeping the old query param working, then update the templates and JavaScript to use the new URL structure. I also need to fix the runs template filter dropdown—it currently passes `dir` to `filterByProject`, but with the new URLs it should pass `label` instead, which means changing the dropdown value from `{{.Dir}}` to the project label.\n\nNow I'm thinking through what needs to change in the template: `ProjectFilter` should represent the label rather than the directory, the dropdown options should use label as their value, and the JavaScript function should redirect to the new `/projects/{label}/runs` path.\n\nFor the \"All projects\" case, that would route to just `/runs`. My plan is to register the new routes in the handler, create handlers that resolve the label to get the appropriate runs, and render or return the data. I could keep the old `?project=` parameter working for backward compatibility while updating all the links to use the new URL structure.\n\nLooking at the template, I can reuse the same runs template for the project-filtered view since it already has the project filter dropdown. The key change is making sure `ProjectFilter` contains the label rather than the directory name, so the select dropdown values match the new URL scheme.\n\nImplementing the handler now...\n\nAdding the new routes and handler...\n\nI'm realizing there's a problem with `resolveProjectDir` — it returns JSON error responses, but the HTML handler needs to return HTML instead when a project isn't found. Let me check what `resolveProjectDir` actually does and whether I need to adjust it or create a separate helper for the HTML path.\n\nFor the template changes, I need to update the dropdown to use the project label instead of the directory as the filter value, and adjust the JavaScript function that handles the filtering accordingly. Updating the template links in both `projects.html` and `project_detail.html` to use the new URL structure with `{{.Label}}` instead of the query parameter approach. I can see that `project_detail.html` already has access to the label through the data passed from `handleProjectDetail`, so the change is straightforward across both templates.\n\nFor the routing, I'll keep the old `/runs?project=` endpoint working for backward compatibility while making the new `/projects/{name}/runs` path the primary one that templates point to. The existing `handleRunsList` doesn't need changes since it already handles the query parameter case.\n\nThe key insight is that the template always needs to compare against labels for the dropdown selection state, so I should convert any incoming directory values to labels before passing them to the template. I'm considering whether to redirect old-style URLs to the new format or just handle the conversion internally—redirecting would be cleaner since it ensures only one code path exists.\n\nWriting the redirect handler... I'm going to take a cleaner approach here: add the new routes for project-filtered runs, update all templates to point to the new URLs, and strip out the `?project=` query parameter handling from the existing endpoints since we're moving to the new structure. I should check what the tests expect and update them accordingly to match this cleaner implementation. I'm reconsidering the backward compatibility approach—I'll have the old `?project=` URLs redirect to the new cleaner routes rather than removing support entirely. For the handlers, I'll strip query parameter filtering from `handleRunsList` and `handleAPIRuns` so they only show all runs, then create new handlers for the project-specific filtered views.\n\nWriting the handler functions... I see that `resolveProjectDir` already handles errors by writing JSON responses, so I'll follow that existing pattern even though it means HTML handlers might return JSON errors. Now I'm planning the implementation: I'll add new routes for project-specific runs, modify the existing handlers to remove project filter query parameter support, and create dedicated handlers for the filtered view. The template changes will update the dropdown to use the new URL structure and adjust the filtering logic accordingly. I'm noticing there's duplicated logic between `handleRunsList` and `handleProjectRuns` for fetching projects, building labels, calculating container counts, and sorting the project list. I should extract this into a helper method to keep the code DRY and maintainable.\n\nActually, the duplication is small enough that I can just leave it as is without over-engineering a solution. Let me think through how `handleRunsList` would work after removing the project filter—it would fetch all runs, get the projects and their labels, count containers per project, and build the sorted project list.\n\nRefactoring the handler to work without the project filter... I'm realizing there's a distinction between the container counts shown in the dropdown versus the runs being displayed—for the `/runs` endpoint showing all runs, I can use the filtered `runs` directly, but for project-filtered pages, I need to think through whether the dropdown should show counts across all projects or just the current filter.\n\nLooking at the template, the dropdown always renders all projects, so I need to compute container counts across all runs regardless of filtering. For `handleProjectRuns`, I'll keep using `allRuns` for the dropdown counts to maintain consistency.\n\nNow I'm going to write the code, and I'm also thinking about backward compatibility—I should add a redirect in `handleRunsList` to support the old `?project=` query parameter.\n\nWriting the handler code...\n\nI'm realizing I need to handle URL escaping for project labels in the redirect. The existing routes already use labels directly in URLs without escaping, so labels are expected to be URL-safe. Since they're derived from filesystem paths, they shouldn't contain problematic characters, but I should still be consistent with how the rest of the codebase handles this.\n\nActually, I'll skip the escaping to match the existing pattern and keep the redirect simple. Now I need to apply the same redirect logic to the API endpoint.\n\nWriting API redirect handler... I'm settling on a simpler approach: add the new routes alongside the old ones, strip out the query parameter filtering from the existing handlers, and update the templates to use the new URLs. No redirects needed—if someone hits the old endpoint, they'll just see all runs instead of filtered results, which is acceptable for this migration.\n\nNow I'm starting to implement this by simplifying the `handleRunsList` handler.\n\nSimplifying the handler...\n\nI'm finishing up the project list by populating each entry with its container count, then sorting alphabetically by label. After that, I'm preparing the template data with the runs, projects, and labels, setting the content type header, and rendering the layout template to the response.\n\nNow I'm realizing that since we're already listing all runs for the container counts, we don't need a separate `allRuns` variable—`runs` can serve that purpose directly. For the `handleProjectRuns` function, I'm fetching the runs for a specific project, getting the full project list to extract labels, and building out the container counts map...\n\nBuilding the handler logic... Building the handler response... Writing template links... I'm updating the polling logic to construct the correct API endpoint based on whether a project filter is active, using the new URL structure with the project name in the path rather than as a query parameter. Now I need to update the tests to reflect these routing changes—the project filter tests should use the new `/projects/{name}/runs` paths instead of query parameters, while keeping the existing container count test as-is since it still works with the base `/runs` route. After that, I'll implement all the changes and review the existing test at line 286 to ensure it aligns with the new structure.\n\nUpdating test requests...","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":38240,"cache_read_input_tokens":17392,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephem